## grid size
dx = 128
dy = 128
n = (dx, 1, dy)
d = (15.0, 10.0, 15.0) # in meters

# # rescale permeability
# BroadK_rescaled = BroadK[:, 1:dx, 256-dy+1:256]

# ## permeability
# K = md * BroadK_rescaled

# print(size(K))
# print(size(BroadK_rescaled))
ϕ = 0.25 * ones(n)
model = jutulModel(n, d, vec(ϕ), K1to3(K))

## simulation time steppings
tstep = 100 * ones(10) #in days
tot_time = sum(tstep)

Parameter setting for Fisher Information Computation¶

In [36]:
nsample = 1
nobs = 5
# # Number of eigenvalues and eigenvectors to compute
nev = 5
tstep = 100 * ones(1) #in days
# tstep = 1 * ones(1) #in days
nt = length(tstep)
μ = 0.0   # Mean of the noise
σ = 1.0   # Standard deviation of the noise
ϕ = 0.25 * ones(n)
dist = Normal(μ, σ)
Out[36]:
Normal{Float64}(μ=0.0, σ=1.0)

FIM in scalable form¶

In [40]:
Ks = zeros(n[1], n[end], nsample);
eigvec_save = zeros(n[1], n[end], nev, 8);
one_Jvs = zeros(n[1]*n[end], nev, 8);
conc = zeros(n[1], n[end], 1);

for i = 1:nsample # 13
    Base.flush(Base.stdout)

    println("sample $(i)")
    # update model for different sample of K
    model = jutulModel(n, d, vec(ϕ), K1to3(K))
    S = jutulModeling(model, tstep)

    # 1. compute forward: input = K
    mesh = CartesianMesh(model)
    logTrans(x) = log.(KtoTrans(mesh, K1to3(x)))
    state0 = jutulSimpleState(model)
    # Initialize an array to store the states at each time step
    states = []

    # Repeat for 8 time steps
    for time_step in 1:1#8
        println("time step $(time_step)")
        # current time step saturation
        @time state(x) = S(logTrans(x), model.ϕ, q; state0 = state0)[1:n[1]*n[3]*1] # shape: 64 x 64 x 16
        @time pressure(x) = S(logTrans(x), model.ϕ, q; state0 = state0)[1+n[1]*n[3]:n[1]*n[3]*2]

        state0_temp = deepcopy(state0)
        state0_temp[1:n[1]*n[3]*1] = state(K)  # Update state0
        state0_temp[1+n[1]*n[3]:n[1]*n[3]*2] = pressure(K)
        cur_state = deepcopy(state0_temp[1:n[1]*n[3]*1])
        push!(states, cur_state)  # Store the current state in the states array

        # compute derivative of log likelihood
        dll = zeros(n[1]*n[end], nev);
        # 2. compute FIM
        for j = 1:nobs
            println("perturbation $(j)")
            noise = rand(dist, size(cur_state)) #.* 0.0001
            # 2-1. compute log likelihood
            ll(x) = norm(vec(cur_state+noise) - state(x)) / (2 * σ^2) 
            # 2-2. compute gradient
            @time outer_vector = Zygote.gradient((x)->ll(x), vec(K))[1]
            # 2-3. save dll
            dll[:, j] = deepcopy(outer_vector)
        end

        # 3. Compute the top three eigenvalues and eigenvectors
        println("shape of Q", size(dll))
        @time U_svd, S_svd, VT_svd = LinearAlgebra.svd(dll)
        println("shape of U (left singular vectors)", size(U_svd))

        eigvec_save[:,:, :, time_step] = reshape(U_svd, n[1], n[end], nev)

        # 4. Compute vjp
        Fv, Fp = Zygote.pullback(state, vec(K)) 
        for e in 1:nev
            println("size lsv", size(U_svd[:, e]))
            col_U = U_svd[:,e]
            @time Jv1 = Fp(col_U)[1]
            println("size", size(Jv1))
            one_Jvs[:, e, time_step] = Jv1
        end
        state0 = deepcopy(state0_temp)
    end
end
